{"word":"ἀνάξιος","slug":"ἀνάξιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνάξιος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>of persons,<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unworthy, not deemed</i> or <i>held worthy of</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἀνάξιον σοῦ</el> <i>too good for</i> thee, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>ἀνάξιος δυστυχεῖν</el> <i>undeserving</i> to suffer, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀναξίως ἑωυτῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>unworthy, worthless</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>undeserving of evil</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>undeserved</i>, <el>ἀνάξια παθεῖν</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}